---
// Three card section
---

<section id="faq" class="bg-white dark:bg-black border-b dark:border-zinc-800 py-8">
  <div class="container mx-auto flex flex-wrap pt-4 pb-12">
    <h2
      class="w-full my-2 text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-center text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100"
    >
      FAQ
    </h2>
    <div class="w-full mb-4">
      <div
        class="h-1 mx-auto gradient w-64 opacity-25 my-0 py-0 rounded-t"
      ></div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 p-6">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 shadow rounded-2xl overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:gap-4 py-6">
          <p class="w-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs md:text-sm px-6 mt-6 uppercase tracking-wide">
            THE BASICS
          </p>
          <div class="w-full font-bold text-xl text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 px-6">
            What is Nostr?
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-base leading-relaxed px-6 mb-8">
            Nostr is <a href="https://nostr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">an open protocol</a> with a chance of working. A simple standard that defines a scalable architecture of clients and servers that can be used to spread information freely. Anyone can build on it, and anyone can use it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 p-6">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 shadow rounded-2xl overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:gap-4 py-6">
          <p class="w-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs md:text-sm px-6 mt-6 uppercase tracking-wide">
            THE APP
          </p>
          <div class="w-full font-bold text-xl text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 px-6">
            Why Boris?
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-base leading-relaxed px-6 mb-8">
            Boris is the reading app I always wanted to have. I had <a href="https://read.withboris.com/a/naddr1qvzqqqr4gupzqmjxss3dld622uu8q25gywum9qtg4w4cv4064jmg20xsac2aam5nqqxnzd3cxqmrzv3exgmr2wfesgsmew" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">this idea</a> for <a href="https://read.withboris.com/a/naddr1qqsxzttkd9ekjmmw94nx7u3dvykhvctvw4jj6etwv93xcety94mk2cszyphydppzm7m554ecwq4gsgaek2qk32atse2l4t9ks57dpms4mmhfxqcyqqq823c59stcz" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">a reading app</a> for a long time, and now I finally sat down and built it. The name comes from <a href="https://relay.dergigi.com/03e174145e1f410772bb8c3e79b153ac0077fe482d7006b1f0ed67a81d475bb9.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">a hallucinated answer</a> to the question "Who invented the highlight marker?".
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 p-6">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 shadow rounded-2xl overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:gap-4 py-6">
          <p class="w-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs md:text-sm px-6 mt-6 uppercase tracking-wide">
            THE NOSTR WAY
          </p>
          <div class="w-full font-bold text-xl text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 px-6">
            What about privacy?
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-base leading-relaxed px-6 mb-8">
            Boris is a nostr client, which means that all highlights and annotations are public by default. While nostr supports private bookmarks, your highlights and annotations are public, just like your notes and posts. Boris adheres to <a href="https://nostrbook.dev/kinds/9802" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">NIP-84</a> and publishes highlights and annotations to your relays.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

